The Boston Celtics blew out the Toronto Raptors 107-89 behind impressive performances from the Celtics starting backcourt. Celtics point guard Rajon Rondo dished out 20 assists and shooting guard Jason Terry provided much of the scoring as he finished with a game-high 20 points. The Raptors, now 2-7 to start the season, really needed more out of their starting front court as Andrea Bargnani, Dominic McGuire, and Jonas Valanciunas combined for 20 points and 8 rebounds
